         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is concerned with numerical integration of continuous functions over the unit square $U^2$. The concept of the $r$th-order blending rectangle rule is introduced by carrying over the idea from Boolean interpolation. Error bounds are developed, and it is shown that $r$th-order blending rectangle rules are comparable with number-theoretic cubature rules. Moreover, $r$th-order blending midpoint rules are defined and compared with the $r$th-order blending rectangle rules.</p>
          </abstract>
